history.content:
The only sections you will able to enroll into are the lecture, 999 discussion and 999L lab sections. For your own scheduling purposes, you can see the days/times for the actual sections but you won't be able to enroll into those via CalCentral.

Each class handles section assignments differently but most CompSci faculty are using SignMeUp (I believe) to do actual section assignments. You will either be notified via email, see the info on the class webpage, or be told during the first lecture how this will happen.

Hi! I wanted to double check about enrollment procedures for CS61C for Spring 2019. I read the post that said to sign up for the 999 lab and discussion, but I just wanted to make sure- is this just the general enrollment procedure, or do you only do this if all the other lab/discussion sections are filled (because they have labs/discussion sections listed on CalCentral)? Also, is there any information about how lab and discussion sections for CS61C in particular will be assigned? Thank you!
